Description: Fix CVE-2026-5079 - DoS via deeply nested field names
 Multer is vulnerable to a denial of service via deeply nested field names
 in multipart/form-data input. An attacker can craft field names with many
 nesting levels (e.g. "a[0][0][0]...") to force append-field to perform
 expensive recursion, exhausting CPU/memory.
 .
 This patch adds a new "fieldNestingDepth" limit option. When set, multer
 rejects field names whose bracket-nesting depth exceeds the configured
 limit with a new LIMIT_FIELD_NESTING error code. When unset, behavior is
 unchanged (unlimited nesting) for backward compatibility.
 .
 Only the security-relevant subset of upstream commit
 a192b5278f240967f5eb13dd1e9a413b4e1b6533 is applied; unrelated refactors
 (abortWithError lifecycle, defParamCharset, extend->spread, README) are
 omitted.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/expressjs/multer/commit/a192b5278f240967f5eb13dd1e9a413b4e1b6533
Bug: https://github.com/expressjs/multer/security/advisories/GHSA-72gw-mp4g-v24j
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-07-07

